36
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:08,290
ANNOUNCER: <i>WJBP, Channel 11.</i>

37
00:04:08,457 --> 00:04:09,754
A quiet South Hartford community

38
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:13,428
was leveled by tragedy as
three clergy members were found dead.

39
00:04:13,503 --> 00:04:16,256
At about 11:47 p.m.
on Sunday evening, the 20th,

40
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:19,684
we received an emergency call
on our 911 line.

41
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:22,434
REPORTER: <i>At least three bodies
were taken out of this house,</i>

42
00:04:22,512 --> 00:04:24,105
<i>two local priests and a nun.</i>

43
00:04:24,181 --> 00:04:26,934
We checked the location for any
other victims and have not found any.

44
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:28,982
REPORTER: <i>Apparently,
Maria Rossi was hosting</i>

45
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:30,778
<i>a church group meeting at her home.</i>

46
00:04:30,854 --> 00:04:33,482
Our homicide detectives
and our lab people

47
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:34,657
<i>are conducting their investigation.</i>

48
00:04:34,733 --> 00:04:37,236
REPORTER: <i>Mrs. Rossi was found
by police in a crawl space.</i>

49
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,404
We can't speculate <i>as</i> to what

50
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:41,156
<i>the cause or the motive may have been.</i>

51
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:43,082
They are not ruling out any possibilities.

52
00:04:44,034 --> 00:04:46,412
<i>However, at this time,
we don't want to speculate</i>

53
00:04:46,495 --> 00:04:49,374
<i>on what may or may not have been
the cause.</i>

54
00:04:53,251 --> 00:04:55,925
<i>My name is Isabella Rossi</i>

55
00:04:56,588 --> 00:04:58,386
and that was my mother.

56
00:04:59,758 --> 00:05:02,386
<i>The thing you have to understand
about my mother</i>

57
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:04,392
is that she just had a huge heart.

58
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:08,935
(SINGING) <i>Down came the rain
and washed the spider out</i>

59
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:12,111
<i>Out came the sun
and dried up all the rain</i>

60
00:05:13,063 --> 00:05:16,613
And there we are.
That was actually on my...

61
00:05:16,942 --> 00:05:18,285
Can you see that?

62
00:05:19,903 --> 00:05:21,951
That was my first birthday party.

63
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,123
<i>And I don't think it was until I was</i>

64
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:28,170
about six years old that
I actually started to notice, you know,

65
00:05:28,245 --> 00:05:30,668
<i>something was different,
her moods were changing.</i>

66
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:32,215
<i>Then, she went away for a little bit</i>

67
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:34,258
<i>and when she came back
they said she was better.</i>

68
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:37,171
But she wasn't.

69
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:39,631
<i>We couldn't understand
what was happening.</i>

70
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:41,136
<i>No one had answers.</i>

71
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:43,639
MICHAEL SCHAEFER:
So why are you doing this film?

72
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:46,805
Because I really need to

73
00:05:47,973 --> 00:05:51,318
understand what happened.

74
00:05:57,148 --> 00:05:59,321
What Maria Rossi did,
and her subsequent life,

75
00:05:59,484 --> 00:06:02,784
was incredibly tragic and clouded.

76
00:06:03,113 --> 00:06:07,493
And caught in the middle of it
is a daughter who is just now learning

77
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,374
<i>the circumstances of that tragedy.</i>

78
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:12,005
MARIA: <i>Isabella,
look at the camera, honey.</i>

79
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:15,213
<i>If someone had asked me</i>

80
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:19,718
how is it possible for Mrs. Rossi
to have done what she did,

81
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:23,517
I would have gone through the list
of things that cause human aggression.

82
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:27,012
Something like major depression,
or schizophrenia,

83
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:29,393
<i>or dissociative identity disorder.</i>

84
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:30,724
<i>It's my understanding</i>

85
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:33,856
that her current psychiatric diagnosis
has been D.I.D.

86
00:06:34,603 --> 00:06:38,653
But this is her seventh different
diagnosis since 1987.

87
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:42,574
ISABELLA: <i>You start wondering,
is it in my genes?</i>

88
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:46,661
You know,
am I going to flip out one day?

89
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:48,541
<i>Just a matter of time?</i>

90
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:53,880
Two years after she brutally murdered
three people in her home,

91
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:55,172
a South Hartford jury

92
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:58,343
<i>found Maria Rossi not guilty
by reason of insanity.</i>

93
00:06:58,585 --> 00:07:01,464
Rossi was committed
to the South Hartford State Asylum.

94
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:03,173
ISABELLA: <i>And then in September
of that year,</i>

95
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:04,424
<i>my mother was transferred</i>

96
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:08,262
to the Centrino Mental Hospital
for the Criminally Insane in Rome, Italy.

97
00:07:08,345 --> 00:07:11,690
<i>I never really questioned why Italy.</i>

98
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,901
MICHAEL: When did your father tell you
what really happened?

99
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:22,409
May 23, 2009. I was 25 years old.

100
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:25,699
<i>He just said it. He said,</i>

101
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:30,208
"Mom attacked those people
during an exorcism."

102
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:33,750
An exorcism performed on her.

103
00:07:33,912 --> 00:07:35,960
It's the job of science to try to sort out

104
00:07:36,039 --> 00:07:38,508
what is a reasonable,
plausible explanation.

105
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:40,794
But science can't explain everything,

106
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:42,003
such as a person

107
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:44,806
levitating two feet off the ground
during an exorcism.

108
00:07:46,675 --> 00:07:50,020
I asked my dad if he thought
she was possessed.

109
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,267
He said he didn't know.

110
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:55,601
That she was gone. It didn't matter.

111
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:57,444
Not any more.

112
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:02,399
He died three days later.

113
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:09,368
<i>I called the church
where the priests had come from.</i>

114
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:10,664
<i>And they wouldn't talk about it.</i>

115
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,789
<i>They said they don't have
an ordained exorcist and never did.</i>

116
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:18,124
So we're on our way to see
the Vatican School for Exorcism.

117
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:20,466
And to see my mother.

118
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:23,136
MICHAEL: Are you nervous?

119
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:28,141
Yeah, I'm nervous.
Twenty years is a long time, you know?

120
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:32,471
<i>So, later, I was contacted
by the Diocese of Rome.</i>

121
00:08:32,554 --> 00:08:36,309
<i>They told me they never authorized
my mother's exorcism.</i>

122
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:39,815
<i>That's when I knew I had to go to Italy.</i>

123
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:52,624
I wonder how seriously they take
the exorcism school, you know.

124
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:56,961
I hope it's not a joke.

125
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:02,380
(BLOWING WHISTLE)

126
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:05,466
Oh, wow.

127
00:09:09,632 --> 00:09:12,476
There it is, St. Peter's Square.

128
00:09:13,845 --> 00:09:15,643
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

129
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:19,150
Something like that.

130
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:29,448
ISABELLA: <i>This school has drawn
a lot of interest from all over the world.</i>

131
00:09:31,196 --> 00:09:34,166
<i>Maybe it can help me understand
my mother's situation a little better.</i>

132
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:37,411
FATHER ROBERT GALLO: From
post-traumatic shock to serious injury,

133
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:38,837
death even.

134
00:09:39,162 --> 00:09:41,836
And not just for the victim.

135
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:46,925
Also for the family members,
for anyone in the vicinity,

136
00:09:47,003 --> 00:09:49,005
especially the priest.

137
00:09:50,006 --> 00:09:52,350
Sometimes a person

138
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:56,354
can be tormented
by more than one demon

139
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:59,524
in what we call
multiple demonic possession.

140
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:03,520
These cases are extremely
volatile and dangerous,

141
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:07,524
and they sometimes
lead to transference,

142
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:11,536
which means
the demon jumps from one person

143
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:13,280
to another.

144
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:19,040
The purpose of the class
is to educate priests

145
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:20,416
and, of course, laypeople,

146
00:10:20,495 --> 00:10:23,749
about the Devil's presence in their lives,
in modern society.

147
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:25,963
<i>For example, in Italy alone</i>

148
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:28,966
<i>there are over 800 satanic cults
We had a problem.</i>

149
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,013
We needed more exorcists.

150
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:33,592
<i>If it is possession,
then first and foremost</i>

151
00:10:33,675 --> 00:10:35,518
<i>we must rule out mental illness.</i>

152
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:37,641
<i>Schizophrenia. Bipolar disorder.</i>

153
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:41,183
<i>The course is designed
to explore all these conditions.</i>

154
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:43,150
(SHOUTING ON TAPE)

155
00:10:48,523 --> 00:10:49,649
(IN ITALIAN)

156
00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:50,984
(MRS. SORLINI SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

157
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,073
(GAGGING)

158
00:10:58,158 --> 00:10:59,535
(SNARLING)

159
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:01,915
Momma.

160
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,081
(RETCHING)

161
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:08,501
(LAUGHING IN SQUEAKY VOICE)

162
00:11:08,585 --> 00:11:10,007
(MRS. SORLINI SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

163
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:11,508
(IN ENGLISH)

164
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:17,181
(CRASHING)

165
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:21,477
Okay, anyone, any thoughts on that?

166
00:11:21,973 --> 00:11:24,271
I believe the subject
was clearly possessed.

167
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,148
The subject
spoke in multiple languages.

168
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:29,781
Come on. Speaking in tongues? Maybe.

169
00:11:30,607 --> 00:11:35,534
Incoherent babbling from
a mentally-disturbed person, certainly.

170
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:36,904
I'm sorry, Father.

171
00:11:36,988 --> 00:11:38,911
And the subject displayed
abnormal strength

172
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:41,994
when confronted with holy water,
and while heavily sedated.

173
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:44,750
The delusional mind
of a paranoid schizophrenic

174
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:48,212
may actually react to holy water
as if it were,

175
00:11:48,291 --> 00:11:50,885
I don't know, acid, urine.

176
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,304
I'm sorry, I'm gonna have to disagree.

177
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:56,304
The girl fractured her own femur.

178
00:11:56,633 --> 00:12:00,479
Her strength might have been abnormal,
but not impossible.

179
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:03,022
It's very well known that

180
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:07,815
some epileptics do break their bones
during a seizure. It's a fact.

181
00:12:08,311 --> 00:12:11,656
GALLO: As I said, we must be sure
to rule out mental illness.

182
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:16,327
In the end, this case
could not be proved as possession.

183
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:19,330
ISABELLA: <i>- The diversity of the class
was comforting.</i>

184
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:22,750
<i>It wasn't just priests or nuns,
but regular people,</i>

185
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:25,499
<i>people who are facing
the same things I'm facing.</i>

186
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:28,832
<i>People like me,
looking to help someone.</i>

187
00:12:29,666 --> 00:12:31,009
ISABELLA: So why are you here?

188
00:12:32,669 --> 00:12:35,047
All this knowledge, you all agree on this,

189
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:38,133
all this knowledge
is invaluable for us, no?

190
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:41,302
David, what would you say
drew you to this school?

191
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:43,559
In particular, to exorcism?

192
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:48,731
The combination
of science and religion.

193
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,609
I think,
based on my background in medicine,

194
00:12:51,688 --> 00:12:53,736
it gave me a greater sense of purpose.

195
00:12:53,815 --> 00:12:57,820
We all talk so definitively
about God and about the Devil

196
00:12:57,902 --> 00:13:03,875
but we can all agree that there's
no real facts, right? No proofs?

197
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:07,754
God has never helped me.
What about you?

198
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:12,417
Sure. Yeah.

199
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:17,221
So when do you actually witness
an exorcism in class?

200
00:13:17,422 --> 00:13:19,424
This class is all theory.

201
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:22,101
This is a school of exorcism, is it not?

202
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:24,725
It's not reality.

203
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,934
Look at the tape we watched today.

204
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:34,072
That girl fit every criteria for possession
except she wasn't.

205
00:13:34,272 --> 00:13:35,524
It's a mental disorder.

206
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:38,576
No. When you witness
someone possessed,

207
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:40,153
you'll know the difference.

208
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:42,330
You say that like you have.

209
00:13:42,405 --> 00:13:45,375
Have you witnessed a real exorcism,
Father?

210
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:51,585
Yeah. Right after he saw
the Easter Bunny.

211
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:54,508
I may have.
Can I ask you something, Isabella?

212
00:13:54,584 --> 00:13:56,052
- Sure.
- I'm curious.

213
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:59,259
Why are you doing this documentary?

214
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:04,803
I will be honest. My mom.

215
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:09,307
When I was about eight years old

216
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:12,272
she murdered three people.

217
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:14,611
Members of her church.

218
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:20,322
I found out that she had committed
these murders during an exorcism.

219
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:23,655
An exorcism on her.

220
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:26,828
- See you.
- It was nice meeting you.

221
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:29,869
Your mother must be at Centrino, right?

222
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:32,793
- Have you seen her yet?
- Tomorrow.

223
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:37,260
Okay, well, the class
won't give you the answers you need.

224
00:14:37,335 --> 00:14:39,383
You need to see a real one.

225
00:14:40,463 --> 00:14:42,215
How do you know when it's real?

226
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:43,637
You know.

227
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:45,222
Good luck.

228
00:14:45,676 --> 00:14:47,019
Thanks.

229
00:14:48,346 --> 00:14:49,598
(SIGHS)

230
00:14:52,558 --> 00:14:54,481
That was interesting.

231
00:15:00,650 --> 00:15:02,493
- Hey.
MICHAEL: - What are you looking at?

232
00:15:02,944 --> 00:15:06,289
My mother's hospital instruction manual.

233
00:15:06,614 --> 00:15:08,491
Look at this thing, it's huge.

234
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:09,826
Okay.

235
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:13,796
So, camera one, two and three.

236
00:15:14,497 --> 00:15:15,498
Which one do I look at?

237
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:17,049
MICHAEL: You don't have to look
directly at the camera.

238
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:18,468
Right. I knew that.

239
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:21,462
MICHAEL: Remember, the cameras
are always running when the car's on.

240
00:15:21,546 --> 00:15:22,593
Let's go.

241
00:15:22,797 --> 00:15:26,973
You know,
my father received a letter from Rome.

242
00:15:27,385 --> 00:15:31,731
I guess because priests were involved.
The Holy Church got involved <i>as</i> well.

243
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:34,647
And they said that they wanted to
